             The BP Plc oil spill is playing out 
like a bad summer movie up and down the Gulf of Mexico’s 1,631 
miles of U.S. coastline. The region’s tourism and commercial 
fishing industries have taken major hits, leaving many 
proprietors wondering if they can remain in business. (Source: 
Bloomberg)  
